Truck drivers blocked the N3 (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - The Road Traffic Management Corporation and other law enforcement agencies have reopened the N3 highway following the latest truck blockade. Rows of trucks lined traffic lanes in both directions between Warden and Villiers in the Free State on Tuesday. READ: N3 blocked between Warden and Villiers Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has condemned the truck drivers’ actions. In a statement released, Mbalula says he is working with Labour Minister, Thulas Nxesi, and Home Affairs Minister, Aaron Motsoaledi to address the truck drivers’ grievances. The Road Traffic Management Corporation and other law enforcement agencies have reopened the N3 highway following the latest truck blockade.Rows of trucks lined traffic lanes in both directions between Warden and Villiers in the Free State earlier today. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/aSVGNNcbhC